I just started intramural volleyball this term. #Interns frequently have dinner together too.
Being here at #JSC has shown me that I still have a lot to learn. Also, what I'm learning in school has real world applications!
Everyone here is so nice and willing to help. I don't know if I've worked with a nicer group of people! https://t.co/gHf3hOXvjD
I am currently working on redesigning one of the spacesuit batteries, which requires a lot of 3D design work.
There are always events and special exhibitions around campus. One day I had a whole conversation with a shuttle #astronaut!
I also take apart cells to look for abnormalities and catalog their general makeup. https://t.co/dxoVe3dE3b
One test involves intentionally setting a cell in thermal runaway to make sure it doesn't cause others to go off. https://t.co/X628kWHTHA
This past year at school, I participated in undergraduate research and setting up a women's mentoring program.
I work in the Propulsion and Power division studying battery safety. Our main concern right now is thermal runaway. https://t.co/wMnPWjzUCf
I study #MechanicalEngineering at IUPUI. @iupui_engrtech.
Hey @NASAJSCstudents followers! This is Stephanie Scharf and today I'll be tweeting about my life as a #NASAintern!
Thanks for hanging out with me on my Twitter takeover! To learn more about being a #NASAIntern, go to: https://t.co/1NCRpH1lib
#nasaintern #jsc http://t.co/3HLSG6kNTn
Daily after work, I exercise at the Gilruth Center. I love running trails @NASA_Johnson. I'm on an intern intramural volleyball team, too!
My favorite place on site is @Space_Station Mission Control. It's manned 24 hours a day to keep astronauts aboard safe at all times.
Coolest thing I've done? Select photos for astronauts to tweet, encouraging students to apply for Micro-g NExT! https://t.co/O82ZkM8FbQ
At work, I also create communication plans to connect other interns. An intern working with interns? You might call it... Intern-ception.
Everyone can agree that one of the coolest parts of working at #JSC is meeting astronauts. Shoutout to @Astro_Clay, one of my #astroheroes!
When I have free time @NASA, I love to attend taste-testing panels. I try the food & rate how I like it before it's sent to @Space_Station!
At work, I get to focus on improving ways the Department of Education communicates to students to get them involved with #NASA and space!
#yhc #nasaintern http://t.co/pdVTmg3qLv
Back at YHC, I double as a theatre major! I love to act, sing, play piano, explore, & spend time with my Gamma Psi sisters & KTO brothers!
As a #NASAIntern, I do communications for the Department of Education. Follow them at @NASA_Edu! #twittertakeover #JSC
